{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the, the train just kept on moving ahead of the Allied armies.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've told you the food situation, and the escaping bit, and the Allied air attacks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it just went on like that, day after day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eventually, we got to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Actually, we'd been moving ahead of the Allied forces, so we were traveling in an easterly direction through various towns.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And eventually we came, actually, to Berlin itself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we saw Berlin totally in ruins-- my birthplace, where I had started off from, originally.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Interesting feeling kind of thing to see it, in, in such a situation.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that, that was roughly the 19th of April.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So it was about two weeks before the Russians got to Berlin, and Hitler killed himself, and all the other events that took place there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we were there right at the end, really.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we went right through Berlin from one end to the other end.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we saw many of the names that we recognized from the past, like Charlottenburg, especially, where I was born in hospital there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then, because the Russians were coming in from the eastern side and the British and Americans from the other side, the train turned south.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then it just carried on and on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mean, we, we just couldn't understand why they were just keeping us, because obviously, it was all coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But our idea is that, that there had been a directive issued from up high, at one time to Kramer in Belsen to say that these exchange people should be kept for potential exchange.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this directive had never been countermanded, so Kramer had played along with it, and everybody else was playing along with it.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
